So when you sell shares and cannot deliver it back to the buyer for which he had already paid money Â  in such a scenario  the exchange calls for an auction. So your broker will try to purchase the shares in a buy-in auction market on T+2 day and the settlement of auction shall be done on T+3 day (holidays are not included).In case of a successful auction  the client in default (i.e. you) will have to pay the actual auction price + Brokerage + Penalty (this depends on your broker).
